{
  "stem": "18960.4",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "As a matter of fact, the so-called [GERMAN], the main guy, was a Jehovah's Witness.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And as it turned out, my kapo who was-- who-- who I was assigned to, to work in the kitchen, to work in the kitchen to do masonry work, he was also a Jehovah's Witness.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "His name was Adam Schmidt.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "Still remember the name.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "He sort of liked me, and he gave me work inside the kitchen, and that was a blessing in the wintertime to work inside the kitchen.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And on top of it, there were some raw vegetables, like carrots and things like that, that I could eat them on the side, that helped me too.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And I was in Wewelsburg-- I was there for a few months.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "A lot of people were killed there, because there was-- there was a lot of stone-- there were stone quarries.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And most of the people were-- had to be-- had too much in the stone quarries.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "And every day, a number of guys were killed-- either died from starvation or from dysentery or from beating.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "And they had to carry him on the-- on their shoulders back to the camp.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "And there was a lot of dysentery there.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "People were dying like flies there from dysentery, from typhoid.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "And I remember, to come back for a moment, when I just came to Wewelsburg, I smelled-- the chimney of the crematorium was apparently active.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "I smelled a burning of like, of nails.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "As it turned out, it was a crematorium, and they were burning all the dead-- dead prisoners.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "I remember once, I had to work in the-- in the so-called [INAUDIBLE] in the-- [INAUDIBLE] was the hospital of the concentration camp.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "And I had to do some masonry work.",
      "word_count": 8
    }
  ],
